HEADWORD: Sarmentose
<hw>Sar`men*tose"</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sarmentosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sarmenteux</ets>. See
<er>Sarment</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Long and
filiform, and almost naked, or having only leaves at the joints where it
strikes root; <as>as, a <ex>sarmentose</ex> stem</as>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Bearing sarments; sarmentaceous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarmentous</ent>⟦br⟧
